                "taskInstruction": "Compress session history only. Use the rendered conversation_history value as the source, preserving any existing summary that is still valid. Read source_run_id and current_session_id from conversation_history metadata. Do not summarize current user_message, Buddy Home, capability_result, or public_response because they are not inputs to this subgraph. Preserve recent raw messages in protected_recent_history Markdown. Summarize middle history, explicit user decisions, task progress, open items, and capability conclusions that already exist in conversation_history into session_summary_candidate Markdown.\n\nWrite all of these outputs: compaction_report JSON with source_run_id, current_session_id, omitted_count, protected_count, summary_changed, summary_source_refs, omitted_refs, protected_recent_history_refs, risk_notes, and anti_thrashing_notes; should_write_summary boolean; writer_input JSON. summary_source_refs, omitted_refs, and protected_recent_history_refs must come from conversation_history.source_refs or conversation_history.context_ref.source_refs. writer_input.commands may contain only one session_summary.update command. payload.content must equal session_summary_candidate. payload.source_refs must equal summary_source_refs. payload.source_run_id must equal conversation_history metadata.source_run_id. payload.session_id must equal conversation_history metadata.current_session_id. change_reason should state that session history reached context pressure and was compacted. If the summary did not materially change or risk is too high, set should_write_summary=false and commands=[].",
